# UI System Standards

- Prefer shadcn/ui primitives before custom components.
- Use shared shells per area:
  - Public shell
  - Patient shell
  - Psychologist shell
  - Manager/Admin shell
- Keep spacing, typography, and colors token-based.
- Use consistent page template:
  1. Title and subtitle
  2. Primary actions
  3. Main content cards/sections
  4. Secondary panels
- Keep table interactions consistent (search/filter/empty/loading/error).
- Keep form behavior consistent (inline validation and clear feedback).
- Do not introduce one-off styling when a shared component exists.

# Accessibility and UX Baseline

- Maintain semantic heading structure.
- Preserve keyboard and focus usability for all interactive controls.
- Ensure good contrast for text and controls.
- Keep RTL compatibility for shared layout/components.
